{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, SPSS 26 software was used for the arithmetic mean, standard deviation, and unrelated measurements in the analysis of the quantitative data.",
    "Fifteen participants attended the focus group interview.",
    "The focus group interview's audio recording was first transcribed, and the qualitative data were analyzed by applying the thematic analysis method, which is a technique that provides a methodical way to create codes and themes and allows researchers to explore, analyze and explain meaningful patterns in qualitative data (Clarke & Braun, 2017).",
    "To ensure inter-rater reliability, as suggested by Terry et al. (2017), two of the authors independently reviewed the transcript several times and performed the coding process in order to determine the relevant themes.",
    "Two researchers met regularly to discuss the findings and construct the themes, and the categories and themes created were periodically discussed with other researchers."
  ]
}